Thu Jun 11 05:20:55 PM CEST 2026
$PROB Datasim
$INPUT NSIM ID TIME RDV DV MDV AMT EVID 
$DATA "data.ferx.csv" IGNORE=@
$SUBROUTINES ADVAN2 TRANS2
$PK
	V  = EXP(THETA(1) + ETA(1));
	KE = EXP(THETA(2) + ETA(2));
	KA = KE + EXP(THETA(3) + ETA(3));
	CL = KE * V;
$ERROR
	CP = A(2)/V;
	Y  = log(CP) + ERR(1);
$THETA
	( 1.61, 3.40, 4.1) ;	/* V */
	( -4.6, -1.2, 0.7) ;	/* KE */
	( -4.6, -0.7, 0.7) ;	/* KA */
$OMEGA BLOCK(3)
	1
	0.001 1
	0.001 0.001 1
$SIGMA
	1
$ESTM SIG=5 MAX=5000 METHOD=1 INTERACT NOABORT POSTHOC PRINT=1

NM-TRAN MESSAGES
  
 WARNINGS AND ERRORS (IF ANY) FOR PROBLEM    1
             
 (WARNING  2) NM-TRAN INFERS THAT THE DATA ARE POPULATION.
             
 (WARNING  23) $PK DOES NOT DEFINE A SCALE PARAMETER FOR THE CENTRAL
 COMPARTMENT.  WITH THIS TRANS, IT MAY NOT BE POSSIBLE TO SEPARATELY
 OBTAIN ESTIMATES OF PARAMETERS AFFECTING CLEARANCE AND VOLUME.
  
Note: Analytical 2nd Derivatives are constructed in FSUBS but are never used.
      You may insert $ABBR DERIV2=NO after the first $PROB to save FSUBS construction and compilation time
  

